### Component 3: Build & Deployment Configuration
We will configure Cloudflare's CLI tool (`wrangler`) to deploy our files. We need to restructure slightly so Wrangler knows which folder holds the "public" HTML vs the backend code.

#### [MODIFY] d:\stitch\node_server\package.json

## Verification Plan

### Local Verification
We will use Cloudflare's local simulator (`npx wrangler pages dev`) to test the backend functions and frontend integration seamlessly on `localhost:8788`.

### Production Deployment
Finally, we will run `npx wrangler pages deploy` to push the site live to the Cloudflare edge, at which point the user can bind their custom domain `cycypher.org` in the dashboard.
